, head to Biharwe Hill, just a short drive away. Visit the 1520 AD Eclipse Monument, a symbolic site marking the solar eclipse that shifted power dynamics among East African kingdoms. Listen to local legends and historical facts from your guide. 
Take in the sweeping views of the Ankole highlands and distant Rwenzori Mountains.

Optionally, explore the ruins of the Biharwe Royal Palace, once a stronghold of Ankole’s rulers, offering insight into Uganda’s royal lineage. By evening you return Journey through the Ankole Countryside
