        (
            [day_number] => 2
            [day_title] => Lubumbashi Tour & Lumumba Assassination Site
            [day_description] => The day starts with a city tour of Lubumbashi, including visits to Sts. Peter and Paul Cathedral, the National Museum, and the Lubumbashi Zoological Garden. After lunch, guests will explore colonial architecture, visit souvenir shops, and head to the Lumumba Assassination Site. This poignant site marks the tragic location where Congo’s first Prime Minister, Patrice Lumumba, was murdered. The day ends with a return to the hotel by late afternoon.
        )

    [2] => Array
        (
            [day_number] => 3
            [day_title] => Likasi and Kyubo Falls
            [day_description] => Day 3 begins with a long drive (six to seven hours) to Kyubo Falls, making stops in Likasi for lunch and a city tour, followed by a visit to the grave of King Msiri in Bunkeya. King Msiri founded the Yeke Kingdom and was a central figure in Katanga's trade history. The day ends with arrival at Kyubo Falls, where guests can begin exploring the area.
        )

    [3] => Array
        (
            [day_number] => 4
            [day_title] => Kyubo Falls and Upemba National Park
            [day_description] => Guests will spend the morning at Kyubo Falls, engaging in various activities like a walk along the river trails, ATV rides, fishing, and canoeing. After lunch, the group will depart for Upemba National Park, known for its diverse ecosystems and wildlife. In the evening, guests meet a local Bayeke family, learning about their culture and traditions.
        )

    [4] => Array
        (
            [day_number] => 5
            [day_title] => Upemba National Park
            [day_description] => This day is dedicated to exploring Upemba National Park. The park’s varied landscapes are home to wildlife such as zebras, antelopes, and buffaloes. Visitors can enjoy guided safaris, explore caves like Tumba and Kiantapo, and visit beautiful waterfalls like Kayo and Ipera. Overnight accommodations in the park offer a chance to enjoy the region's natural beauty in tranquility.
        )

    [5] => Array
        (
            [day_number] => 6
            [day_title] => Drive Back to Lubumbashi
            [day_description] => On Day 6, the group travels back to Lubumbashi, a journey that takes most of the day. The evening is free for rest or additional personal exploration.
        )

    [6] => Array
        (
            [day_number] => 7
            [day_title] => Kundelungu National Park Visit
            [day_description] => A full-day visit to Kundelungu National Park starts with a trip to Lofoi Falls, the highest waterfall in Africa. Travelers will have the chance to spot a wide variety of wildlife, including lions, leopards, and buffaloes, during a 4WD safari. After a visit to the falls, the group enjoys the breathtaking views and a peaceful night at a nearby camp or lodge.
        )

    [7] => Array
        (
            [day_number] => 8
            [day_title] =>  End of Service
            [day_description] => The final day marks the end of the tour, with guests being transferred to the airport for their flight home or to the border if exiting via Zambia. For those continuing their journey, a new itinerary can begin.
        )

